 You have to be careful with it 

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:18.360
 you can't have everything. You can have what would be good for you, but you have to figure out what that is, 

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:20.820
 and then you have to aim for it. 

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:26.860
 Well, my experience with people is that if they figure out what it is that would be good for them and they aim 

00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:30.989
 then they get it. And it's weird because 

00:02:30.989 --> 00:02:32.980
 it's a strange thing, it's not that simple. 

00:02:32.980 --> 00:02:34.980
 Because, for example, you may formulate 

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:37.080
 an idea about what would be good for you 

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:41.069
 and then you take ten steps to that end and you see that your formulation was not entirely correct. 

00:02:41.069 --> 00:02:42.750
 And then you have to reformulate your goal. 

00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:46.559
 You go a bit like that while moving towards your goal. 

00:02:46.930 --> 00:02:50.910
 But one big reason people fail is that they are the 

00:02:51.280 --> 00:02:53.280
 never set criteria for success. 

00:02:53.300 --> 00:03:00.240
 And so, because success is such a narrow line and very unlikely, the chance that you will stumble over it randomly 

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:01.560
 is zero! 

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:08.440
 And so there is a suggestion here and the suggestion is: "If you really want something, 

00:03:08.620 --> 00:03:10.620
 then you can have it! " 

00:03:10.720 --> 00:03:15.640
 The question then is: "What do you mean by really wanting?" 

00:03:16.080 --> 00:03:20.500
 And the answer is that you re-orientate yourself in every possible way, 

00:03:21.240 --> 00:03:26.100
 so that the chance that that happens is as certain as possible. 

