 But asking is not, 

00:03:41.740 --> 00:03:44.060
 a flurry or today's wish. 

00:03:44.340 --> 00:03:50.540
 You have to be dead serious about it. You have to think: "Okay, I'm going to make an inventory of myself 

00:03:50.739 --> 00:03:55.589
 and if I would live suitably in the world and set myself up like that 

00:03:56.160 --> 00:04:02.180
 so that existence would justify itself - in my opinion - and I do not mean as a merciless judge, 

00:04:02.420 --> 00:04:02.920
 what exactly is it that i would aim for? " 

00:04:02.920 --> 00:04:08.100
 Well, one of the things that I found was that ... 

00:04:08.460 --> 00:04:12.960
 To test this theory, 

00:04:13.280 --> 00:04:21.160
 you could try this. This is a form of prayer - knocking - sit down on your bed one day and ask yourself: 

00:04:22.080 --> 00:04:27.180
 What is - what incredibly stupid things I do regularly 

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:29.660
 to completely ruin my life? " 

00:04:29.910 --> 00:04:31.969
 And if you actually ask yourself that question - 

00:04:31.970 --> 00:04:35.569
 You must want to know the answer, right. Because that is what asking the question actually means. 

00:04:35.569 --> 00:04:40.860
 It doesn't just mean saying the words, it means you have to decide that you want to know. 

00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:44.200
 You will find out so quickly that you will be amazed. 

00:04:46.400 --> 00:04:47.120
 It's like... 

00:04:47.240 --> 00:04:51.460
 Jung thought about this, he thought people had two poles of consciousness. 

00:04:51.580 --> 00:04:55.040
 One was the consciousness of the individual with whom we all identify with. 

00:04:55.200 --> 00:04:57.680
 And the other was something he called [the Self] and the Self is the ... 

00:04:57.860 --> 00:05:01.780
 You can see it as the divine within. That is a great approach. 

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:07.759
 It is the universal part of your consciousness. It is your conscience. You can see it that way. 

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:13.600
 Whatever your conscience may be. But it is something you can consult, it is like the daimon of Socrates. 

00:05:13.620 --> 00:05:17.900
 Socrates said it was what made him different from the rest of Greece 

00:05:18.160 --> 00:05:20.740
 was that he consulted his inner daimon, his genius. 

00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:25.300
 He asked himself how it was exactly that he had to behave 

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:29.340
 and then he did that! Whatever it was! He did not try to force a solution. 

00:05:29.430 --> 00:05:33.409
 he did not try to force a solution in a selfish way. He asked: 

00:05:33.409 --> 00:05:38.260
 "I am going to manifest myself in the best possible way in the world, I would like that, 

00:05:38.460 --> 00:05:40.460
 what would that be?" 

00:05:40.620 --> 00:05:47.040
 Well, you are perfectly capable of thinking. God knows how! You are perfectly capable of ... 

00:05:47.240 --> 00:05:52.720
 huge trips of imagination and dreams and fantasies. God knows how to do that. 

00:05:52.919 --> 00:05:58.189
 What would happen if you consult yourself about the best possible outcome for you. Maybe you will get an answer! 

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:00.860
 That is this idea. 

